  "prompt": "Who is the best support hero in Dota 2?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" support hero in Dota 2 can be subjective and highly situational, as it often depends on the current meta, team compositions, and individual player skill. However, some support heroes are frequently praised for their versatility and effectiveness across various situations.\n\nAs of my last knowledge update in October 2023, here are a few support heroes that are often regarded highly:\n\n1. **Earthshaker** - Great team fight potential with his Echo Slam and Fissure to control enemies.\n2. **Lion** - Offers both control with Hex and Mana Drain, as well as burst damage with Finger of Death.\n3. **Shadow Shaman** - Provides effective crowd control and pushing power with Mass Serpent Ward.\n4. **Disruptor** - Excellent at controlling team fights and catching out enemies with Static Storm and Kinetic Field.\n5. **Treant Protector** - Offers great sustain with Living Armor and can be a solid frontliner with his abilities.\n\nUltimately, the best support hero for you may depend on your team's composition and strategy, as well as your personal playstyle and comfort with particular heroes. Keeping an eye on the patch notes and the evolving meta can also help you choose the most effective support hero for your games.",
